  "text": "We next turned our attention to the mechanisms associated with 2-ME-mediated growth inhibition and began by evaluating potential entry into a senescence-like state [CITATION_1] . It was found that 2ME (1.0 M) induced senescence as shown by increased senescence associated Beta-galactosidase (SA-␤gal) blue staining after 5 days of culture ( Fig. 2A) . Treatment of the SK-Mel-28, SK-Mel-103 and SK-Mel-147 with their IC50 value of 2ME showed a higher percentage of SA-␤gal staining compared to the control group (Supplementary Table 1 ). Expression of the senescence marker Histone H3 trimethylated in the Lysine 9 (H3K9Me3), also showed a slight increase following treatment of the cells with 10 M of 2ME for 72 h (Fig. 2B) .",
